# Cline Rules — LinkedIn SSI Booster

# Project: linkedin_ssi_booster

# Author: Shawn Jackson Dyck

# Stack: Python 3.11+, Anthropic Claude API, Buffer GraphQL API

## Project Structure

- All service modules live in `services/` package: `claude_service.py`, `buffer_service.py`, `content_curator.py`, `ssi_tracker.py`
- Root-level orchestration: `main.py`, `scheduler.py`, `content_calendar.py`
- Always import services via `from services.X import Y` — never from root
- Run all scripts from the **project root** so `services/` is on sys.path

## Code Style

- Python 3.11+ syntax preferred
- Type hints on all function signatures
- Use `logging` (not `print`) for diagnostics — logger names match module name
- No bare `except:` — always catch specific exception types
- Constants in UPPER_SNAKE_CASE at module top

## Environment & Secrets

- All secrets loaded via `python-dotenv` from `.env` (never hardcode keys)
- Required env vars: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `BUFFER_API_KEY`
- `.env` is gitignored — use `.env.example` as template

## External APIs

- **Buffer**: GraphQL API at `https://api.buffer.com` — all calls through `BufferService._query()`
- **Anthropic**: Use `ClaudeService` wrapper; default model is `claude-opus-4-5` unless cost-optimisation needed
- Always handle API errors explicitly; surface meaningful messages to the logger

## SSI Focus

Four target components with individual weightings:

- `establish_brand` — post quality, profile completeness
- `find_right_people` — targeting, connection quality
- `engage_with_insights` — article sharing, commenting
- `build_relationships` — DMs, story posts

## Testing

- Prefer `--dry-run` flag pattern for destructive operations (no API calls)
- Unit tests go in `tests/` (create if missing); name files `test_<module>.py`
- Mock external API calls — never hit live Anthropic/Buffer in tests

## After Every Change

- Run `python -m py_compile <changed_files>` after editing any `.py` file and fix all errors before finishing
- Update `README.md` whenever you change how the tool is configured, how a feature works, or what env vars are required — keep the docs in sync with the code

## After Every Code Change

- Always run `python -m py_compile <changed_files>` immediately after editing any `.py` file
- Fix all syntax errors before considering a task complete
- Example: `python -m py_compile services/claude_service.py services/gemini_service.py services/ollama_service.py`

## Do Not

- Do not add `sys.path` hacks in source files — fix the package structure instead
- Do not commit `.env` or any file containing API keys
- Do not generate mock LinkedIn SSI data without a `# NOTE: mock data` comment
